      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The humming noise with no fan movement usually indicates a seized motor, a tripped overload protector, or that a capacitor has failed. Please do **not** approach the unit blindly, as outdoor condensers can harbor high-voltage electricity even after the power is switched off. For safety, turn off the breaker for that circuit and only inspect if you are comfortable with electrical work; otherwise, call a licensed technician immediately.",
